               <p>WILLIAM OSWALD. I lost a handkerchief on the 3d of June, from off the hall table, at Lord Melburne's - I had left it there about three o'clock in the afternoon; I did not see it again till I was at Bow-street, on the 15th of August. The prisoner was coachman to Mr. George Lamb, and used to come there frequently. On the evening I missed it I asked him about it - he said he gave it to Mr. Lamb's footman.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18261026-123-person814">
                  WILLIAM 
                  RICHARDS
               <interp inst="t18261026-123-person814" type="surname" value="RICHARDS"></interp>
